        "id": 8956
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-28T19:55:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I really don\u0027t like an idea of SkUnicode coming to Paragraph from somewhere.\nI have string transformation in ParagraphBuilder (addText) and ParagraphStyle (setEllipsis).\nDo I have to drag SkUnicode all over? I tried and I really don\u0027t like the results (and API changes).\nNow, I have a question: all these complications come from \nvirtual SkString SkStringFromU16String(const std::u16string\u0026 utf16text) \u003d 0;\nCan I use an implementation that has SkUTF::ToUTF8 instead of u_strToUTF8?\nThen it\u0027s not going to depend on ICU at all.",
      "parentUuid": "8b0eabd6_38c98b4f",
      "revId": "80d4a2602959a59fc470e368382e6c588c2d9aee",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "75b7a869_1ab80f16",
        "filename": "modules/skparagraph/src/ParagraphImpl.cpp",
